sentences: Charles Alexander Joel (born 1971 in London, England) is a British/German pianist and conductor.

From 2001 to 2007 he held the position of Erster Kapellmeister at the Deutsche Oper am Rhein in Duesseldorf and DuisburgHe has served as guest conductor for numerous orchestras in Europe and elsewhere, including the Bavarian State Opera, the Sächsische Staatskapelle Dresden, the MDR Symphony Orchestra, the Deutsches Symphonie-Orchester Berlin and the Hamburg State Opera  (Hamburgische Staatsoper).

From 2001 to 2007 he held the position of Erster Kapellmeister at the Deutsche Oper am Rhein in Duesseldorf and DuisburgHe has served as guest conductor for numerous orchestras in Europe and elsewhere, including the Bavarian State Opera, the Sächsische Staatskapelle Dresden, the MDR Symphony Orchestra, the Deutsches Symphonie-Orchester Berlin and the Hamburg State Opera  (Hamburgische Staatsoper).

From the  2007/2008 to the 2013/14 season Alexander Joel was the musical director (Generalmusikdirektor) of Staatstheater Braunschweig and principal conductor of Staatsorchester Braunschweig, succeeding Jonas Alber, who had led the orchestra since 1997.
